# =========================================================================
# Secrets — never commit
# =========================================================================
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*.cer
# Passkey credential store (lives in <PROJECTS_ROOT>/.crc-passkeys.json by
# default, but defended here in case a user reconfigures the path into the
# repo). Contains FIDO2 public-key credentials — not secret on its own but
# personally identifying.
.crc-passkeys.json
# Web Push subscription + VAPID keypair store. The VAPID PRIVATE KEY in
# this file lets anyone send push notifications to subscribed phones —
# never commit it.
.crc-push.json
# Shared secret for the /api/trigger/{token} endpoint. Anyone with this
# token can POST a prompt to the bridge for Claude to run; keep it local.
.crc-trigger-token
# =========================================================================
# Log files at the project root — HARD RULE (user request, twice)
# =========================================================================
# Bridge / server / restart logs must NEVER live at the repo root. They
# always go into `.cache/` (which is `.cache/` -gitignored below). These
# rules are belt-and-suspenders so any stray redirect a launcher might
# accidentally do never ends up in `git status`. If you see a NEW
# pattern of stray log appear, ADD it here — never relax the rule.
#
# Pattern coverage:
#   .bridge.log / .bridge.*.log / bridge.log / bridge.log.err  — Python stdout/stderr
#   .server.log / .server.err / .server.out / .server.*.log    — ad-hoc Start-Process redirects
#   *.out / *.err at the repo root                             — anything else that slips through
bridge.log
bridge.log.err
bridge.out.log
bridge.err.log
/.bridge.log
/.bridge.log.err
/.bridge.err.log
/.bridge.out.log
/.bridge.*.log
.server.log
.server.err
.server.out
.server.err.log
.server.out.log
.server.*.log
/*.out
/*.err
# Rotated/backed-up bridge logs from the (optional) Start-Process
# log-rotation pattern. Same sensitive-data concerns as the live logs.
*.log.bak
*.log.err.bak
# Generated splash artwork — keep the source PNG (octopus.png) tracked so
# new clones can rebuild, but the derived per-device PNGs are large and
# regenerate from a single `python tools/build_splashes.py` run.
# (Comment out the next two lines if you want to ship pre-built splashes.)
# bridge/web/static/splash/splash-*.png

# UI icon build intermediates — the *.raw.png files are the Nano Banana
# output (solid-white-bg PNG). They get processed by the build scripts
# into the tracked transparent-bg .png files alongside them. The raws
# are build inputs only; never served to the client. Cover every icon
# subfolder with a recursive glob so future tools (models, status, etc.)
# don't accidentally check in their raws.
bridge/web/static/icons/**/*.raw.png

# =========================================================================
# Python
# =========================================================================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
.python-version

# =========================================================================
# Node (for the future channel server + any client-side tooling)
# =========================================================================
node_modules/
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# =========================================================================
# Bridge runtime state — regenerated on every run
# =========================================================================
*.log
logs/
bridge_state.json
.last_session_id
.cache/
.web-uploads/

# Empty per-project watch folders (live INSIDE each project under
# PROJECTS_ROOT — not at the bridge root, but if a user's workflow
# accidentally creates them here, don't track).
/assets/
/output/
/screenshots/

# Root-level PNGs are test/debug screenshots dropped by Playwright runs
# and ad-hoc visual probes. Use `/` prefix so this only matches files at
# the repo root — tracked icon PNGs under `bridge/web/static/icons/` and
# `bridge/web/static/splash/` are unaffected. Added 2026-05-17 after a
# security audit caught 13 untracked PNGs that `git add -A` would have
# committed to the public repo.
/*.png
# Same pattern for dotfile logs that the orchestrator's hidden-window
# pythonw launcher drops at the repo root when stdout is captured.
/.bridge.log
/.bridge.err.log
# Tempfile we use as a write-stage for memory files (the .claude/** write
# rail blocks Edit/Write inside that path).
/tmp-*.md
/tmp-*.txt

# Stray Windows redirect artifact ("> nul" in PowerShell creates a file
# named `nul`)
nul

# Asset-version state file. The bridge auto-bumps this on every static
# file mtime change — tracking it would mean every JS / CSS edit shows
# up as an extra dirty file in `git status` and produces a noise-only
# diff in every PR. The bridge creates a fresh file on first request
# if it's missing.
bridge/web/.asset-version

# =========================================================================
# Editor / OS
# =========================================================================
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# =========================================================================
# Developer-only artifacts — NOT shipped to public GitHub
# =========================================================================
# These directories support the bridge maintainer's own workflow on this
# codebase (Claude Code config, design skills, asset-build scripts) but
# are not needed by end users who just want to install + run the bridge.
# A fresh clone of the public repo will not have them; the bridge runtime
# does not depend on any of them — all build outputs (icons, splash PNGs,
# inlined splash markup) are pre-committed under bridge/web/static/.
#
# Each directory still exists on the maintainer's local disk after this
# gitignore takes effect — it's only `git push` / `git status` that
# treats them as invisible.
.claude/
skills/
tools/
CLAUDE.md

# Anything starting with `.local-` is "this developer's machine only"
# (transcripts, exports, debugging dumps you want to keep around but not
# share). Optional convention, but the gitignore reserves it.
.local-*/

# Claude Code project-scoped MCP server list. Dev-only convenience
# (e.g. Playwright MCP for live PWA debugging) — never required to run
# or use the bridge. Each developer adds their own preferred MCPs via
# `claude mcp add --scope project …`.
.mcp.json

# Playwright MCP working directory — created automatically when the
# Playwright MCP is active in the current Claude Code session. Holds
# per-call screenshot scratch and page snapshot YAML dumps. Regenerated
# every run; never needed in git.
.playwright-mcp/

# Detached bridge-restart logs. The PowerShell launcher pipes the
# hidden-window process stdout/stderr into these when restarting the
# bridge; same sensitive-data concerns as bridge.log.* above.
.restart.log
.restart.log.err

# Dev-only output folders. Both regenerate from running the relevant
# tool / launcher and contain noise the public repo doesn't need.
#   logs/             — bridge.log / bridge.log.err / .restart.log* land here when
#                       the bridge is spawned detached via the orchestrator's
#                       hidden-window restart pattern. May contain request
#                       paths, tracebacks referencing local file paths.
#   dev-screenshots/  — every pwa_driver / pwa_visual_probe screenshot run
#                       drops a timestamped subdir here. Grows on the dev's
#                       disk over time; never needed in git. Manual cleanup
#                       with `rm -rf dev-screenshots/` between sessions is fine.
logs/
dev-screenshots/
